result.execSummary:
The defendant Dale L. Samuelson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Dale L. Samuelson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Dale L. Samuelson was found guilty of 940.19 Battery. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Court reviews file, adjourned last time to allow defendant time to fill out waiver of right to counsel. 09:31 AM Defendant Dale L. Samuelson in court.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Dale L. Samuelson appeared by video means. Samuelson wants to waive his right to counsel. Court will set for AIA, defendant needs to appears in person, sets for AIA on 4/13/22 at 11:5 AM.

Must sign and return to the Clerk of Court's Office with in 10 days.

09:15 AM Defendant Dale L. Samuelson appears by video.  Alexander Paul Seifert appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Samuelson has received a copy of complaint. Court reads charges and penalties. Samuelson understands. Court questions if he has contacted an attorney. Samuelson talked to one, consultation with an attorney and will represent himself. Court will have a waiver of attorney sent to him. State thought there was a $650 bond posted. Clerk indicates it was returned. State asks for $1000 signature bond. Court imposes $1000 signature bond, must sign and return to COC within 10 days. Samuelson now would like to possibly be represented. Court explains processes of obtaining an attorney, SPD, private hire or if not eligible can apply for appointment of an attorney through the court. Samuelson thinks he wants to continue on his own. Court explains must fill out waiver of attorney and then he could contact the DA. AIA scheduled 4-6-22 at 9:30 AM. Adjourned 9:21 AM.
